OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,398,390,120,260,000,100
PN,39702
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F397A1773227361
OL,3,CWarrington MP tells Parliament she was
OL,4,Craped while at a work event
OL,6,FIf passed, the measure would see cases
OL,7,Fwith a likely sentence of three years
OL,8,For less being heard by a single crown
OL,9,Fcourt judge.
OL,11,FMs Nichols accused Mr Lammy of using
OL,12,Fvictims as a "cudgel" to drive through
OL,13,Freforms to the courts system, as she
OL,14,Fspoke of her own experience.
OL,16,FShe told the Commons on Tuesday 10
OL,17,FMarch: "I waited 1,088 days to go to
OL,18,Fcourt.
OL,26,@tD@NOUtD@UO]yD@HOU
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G2/6
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,398,390,120,260,000,100
PN,39703
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F397A1773227361
OL,3,CWarrington MP tells Parliament she was
OL,4,Craped while at a work event
OL,6,F"Every single one of those days was
OL,7,Fagony, made worse by having a role in
OL,8,Fpublic life that meant that the mental
OL,9,Fhealth consequences of my trauma were
OL,10,Fplayed out in public, with the event
OL,11,Fthat led to my eventual sectioning for
OL,12,Fmy own safety, still being something
OL,13,Fthat I receive regular social media
OL,14,Fabuse from strangers about to this day.
OL,16,F"But here's the kicker, in this
OL,17,Fdebate, experiences like mine feel
OL,18,Flike they've been weaponised and are
OL,19,Fbeing used for rhetorical
OL,20,Fmisdirection, for what this Bill
OL,21,Factually is.
OL,26,@nD@AOUxD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G3/6
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,398,390,120,260,000,100
PN,39704
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F397A1773227361
OL,3,CWarrington MP tells Parliament she was
OL,4,Craped while at a work event
OL,6,F"The violence against women and girls
OL,7,Fsector haven't had the opportunity to
OL,8,Fcome together to discuss it, and the
OL,9,FGovernment's framing and narrative has
OL,10,Fbeen to pit survivors and defendants
OL,11,Fagainst each other in a way I think is
OL,12,Fdeeply damaging.
OL,14,F"We have been told that if we have
OL,15,Fconcerns about this Bill, it is
OL,16,Fbecause we have not been raped or
OL,17,Fbecause we don't care enough for rape
OL,18,Fvictims.
OL,26,@nD@AOUvD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G4/6
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,398,390,120,260,000,100
PN,39705
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F397A1773227361
OL,3,CWarrington MP tells Parliament she was
OL,4,Craped while at a work event
OL,6,F"The opposite is true in my case, it
OL,7,Fis because I have been raped that I am
OL,8,Fas passionate as I am about what it
OL,9,Fmeans for a justice system to be truly
OL,10,Fvictim focused.
OL,12,F"It is because I have endured every
OL,13,Findignity that our broken criminal
OL,14,Fjustice system could mete out that I
OL,15,Fcare what kind of reform will actually
OL,16,Fdeliver justice for survivors and
OL,17,Fvictims of crime more widely."
OL,26,@tD@AOUyD@^O]
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G5/6
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,398,390,120,260,000,100
PN,39706
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F397A1773227361
OL,3,CWarrington MP tells Parliament she was
OL,4,Craped while at a work event
OL,6,FShe added: "There is so much that we
OL,7,Fcan be doing for rape victims that
OL,8,Fisn't the Lord Chancellor using them
OL,9,Fas a cudgel to drive through reforms
OL,10,Fthat aren't directly relevant to them.
OL,12,F"As a starting point, Rape Crisis
OL,13,FEngland and Wales have called for five
OL,14,Fkey demands in their Living in Limbo
OL,15,Freport. Don't say that this Bill helps
OL,16,Fdeliver justice for rape victims,
OL,17,Funtil it actually, materially does."
OL,26,@nD@LOUtD@AOUyD@dO]
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G6/6
